question: steel-type? :0
answer:
• Metagross (Steel/Psychic): S T R O N K. Also they’ve got Psychic-type moves that can counter any Fighting-type opponents.
  • Aggron (Steel/Rock): Tanky boi. Also has Rock-type moves to counter any Fire-type opponents.
  • Empoleon (Water/Steel): A pretty decent Pokémon with Water-type moves to counter any Fire or Ground-type opponents.
  • Alolan Dugtrio (Ground/Steel): Speedy boi.
  • Aegislash (Steel/Ghost): Can switch from stronk boi to tanky boi. Pretty handy.
  • Scizor (Bug/Steel): Stronk bug. Also has a Mega-Evolution.

summary: Smash Bros Ultimate Now Has A VR Mode
title: Smash Bros Ultimate Now Has A VR Mode
body:
You can sort of play Smash Bros Ultimate in VR as of today…but only a small portion of the game. With the latest update, Nintendo added VR Toy-Con support…..so you would need those cardboard glasses to slip the Switch into. Said support amounts to single-player, limited and timed offline matches — can’t go online with…
